            , to Swear that they saw the Money (37 l. 7 s. 6 d) paid to Constable, at the Royal Oak at Reading, on the 7th of July 1718. A Memorandum sign'd by Nicholson and the prisoner, was forg'd, and hung in the Chimny to make it appear old; when the Trial came on, the prisoner swore to the Payment of the Money, and to other particulars mentioned in the Indictment, but Nicholson instead of Confirming his Evidence, discover'd the whole Management. The prisoners Affidavit was falsify'd by the Evidence of several Witnesses and the Jury found him <rs id="t17220704-33-verdict169" type="verdictDescription">
